Citation.sTitle: Solubility, Density, Refractive Index, Viscosity, and Electrical Conductivity of Boric Acid + Lithium Sulfate + Water System at (293.15, 298.15, 303.15, 308.15 and 313.15) K
Citation.sAbstract: The solubility, density, refractive index, viscosity and electrical conductivity for aqueous solutions of Li2SO4 from (0 to 3.1472) mol*kg 1H2O, saturated in H3BO3, over the temperature range from (293.15 to 313.15) K have been determined. These physical properties were represented by equations as functions of temperature and Li2SO4 concentration. This information is useful for evaluating the physical properties of aqueous solutions saturated in H3BO3 in the range of concentrations of Li2SO4 and temperatures studied.
